    <dlgPart>
      <portrait />
      <speaker_name />
      <npc_text>[success]The man stares at you for a moment, looking for any signs of dishonorable intentions, then gives up and nods. He kneels next to the vanquished construct and goes through his innards in a surprisingly efficient way.

He pulls out different parts, commenting on their design and praising the ingenuity of the ancients, until he finds what he’s looking for. It’s a strange-looking, oil-dripping thingamajig with loose wires. The man wipes out the grease and the oil, ties the wires together, turning it into a handy protection amulet.

“Put it around your neck where they can see it,” he says, looking very pleased with himself.</npc_text>
